Perineal endometrioma occurring during pregnancy: a case report. Perineal endometrioma has been reported in reproductive-aged women following perineal trauma. The common presentation is a perineal mass with cyclic pain coincident with the menstrual cycle in a woman with a history of perineal laceration. Curative treatment is possible with complete surgical excision. No reports of perineal endometrioma occurring during pregnancy have been published before.A case of perineal endometrioma occurred during pregnancy. The patient had a perineal mass that enlarged, with worsening pain.A perineal endometrioma may progress during pregnancy. Proper diagnosis is important, and treatment with surgical excision should be considered before attempting subsequent pregnancies.